        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Following are the Operating Instructions, Transmitter Programming Procedures, Option Programming
                    Procedures, and Circuit Diagram for the Remote Keyless Entry Option on the above referenced models.
                </para>
                <para>Please reference SFN 07-89 for a new diagnostic tool, (Remote Entry Pro) part number 500010 to use
                    as a quick aid to check Key Fob function.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <partsinfo>
            <para>2586513C1, Transmitter, Remote Keyless Entry</para>
            <para>3591609C91, Module with two remote transmitters, replacement for all 9000 Model Series</para>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Operator Instructions for Remote Keyless Entry</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">System Features</emph>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Door Locks</para>
                <para>Doors lock when "LOCK" is pressed.</para>
                <para>Press twice for horn confirmation. (See Programming Option 8)</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Door Unlock</para>
                <para>Driver's door unlocks when "UNLOCK/TRUNK" is pressed once.</para>
                <para>Passenger's door unlocks when "UNLOCK/TRUNK" is pressed and held. Driver's door will unlock when
                    Parking Brake is applied or ignition is turned OFF (See Programming Option 4).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Illuminated Entry</para>
                <para>Courtesy lights turn on when the doors are unlocked with the remote transmitter and will turn off
                    in one minute or:
                </para>
                <para>With Parking Brake released, courtesy lights will turn off as soon as the ignition switch is
                    turned on. If Parking Brake is set, interior lights will turn off when Parking Brake is released.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0308021" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0308021.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="208px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Remote Keyless Entry Transmitter</caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="t0308021">
                <title>Operation Summary</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="0.93*"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.07*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>ACTION</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>RESULT</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Press "LOCK" button once</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Both doors will lock</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Press "LOCK" button twice</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Horn will sound to confirm successful lock</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Press "UNLOCK/TRUNK" button once</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Driver's door will unlock and courtesy lights will turn on for one minute or until
                                    the ignition switch is turned on and Parking Brake is released
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Press "UNLOCK/ TRUNK" and hold</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Passenger's door will unlock</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Press "LOCK" and "UNLOCK/TRUNK" at the same time</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Panic Mode-Horn will pulse off and on until any button is pressed again</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The keyless entry system will not respond to transmitter commands if ignition switch is on and
                        the Parking Brake is released. Doors can be locked and unlocked with transmitter while engine is
                        running if the Parking Brake is applied.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <title>Changing the transmitter battery</title>
            </para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Insert a small coin in case slot on edge of transmitter. Twist to open.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove case backing and locate battery.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remove battery. Replace with GP-23A equivalent. Observe (+) and (-) indicators.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Replace case backing. Press together firmly. Test for operation.</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="program" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Programming Additional Transmitters</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The system module has four memory slots or locations, which allow up to 4 remote transmitters.
                        For proper operation all memory slots must have a transmitter code stored. If only one
                        transmitter is being used, it must be programmed four times; if two transmitters are being used,
                        each must be programmed twice; if three transmitters are being used, one must be programmed
                        twice; if four are being used each must be programmed.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Block the tires so the truck cannot roll.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release the Parking Brake.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the truck's ignition switch to the ON position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the programming connectors #1 and #2 at the top right of the fuse block.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect programming connector #1 with programming connector #2.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After 10-15 seconds, horn will sound 3 times. Disconnect the programming connectors.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press LOCK on the new transmitter(s). Horn will sound 1 time. If additional transmitters
                    are to be programmed, press lock on each new transmitter to be programmed.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the ignition switch OFF.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply the parking brake. Test the remote transmitter for proper operation.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
