            </svcprocinfo>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Changing Programming Options</title>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Chock wheels to prevent vehicle movement.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Release the parking brake.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Turn the truck's ignition switch to the ON position.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Locate the programming circuit connectors at the top right of the fuse block.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Connect together programming connector #1 with programming connector #2.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">After 10-15 seconds, horn will sound 3 times.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Momentarily, disconnect the programming connectors.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Momentarily, reconnect the programming connectors. The horn will sound 4 times. This
                        indicates the system has entered the Options Programming Mode.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Disconnect the programming connectors.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Use a programmed remote transmitter. Press the both buttons to advance to the first
                        and/or next option. The horn will sound to indicate the option number being programmed.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Press the LOCK button to turn the selected option ON or OFF. The vehicle's status
                        light (Located on module harness inside right side kick panel) indicates whether an option is ON
                        or OFF.
                    </para>
                    <randlist type="bullet">
                        <item>
                            <para>If an option is ON the indicator will light.</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>If an option is OFF the indicator will turn off.</para>
                        </item>
                    </randlist>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Turn ignition OFF to end option programming.</para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">Test the remote transmitter for proper operation of programmed functions.</para>
                </step1>
                <figure id="f0308022" figsize="pg-wide">
